<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Bikil</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-12-06 13:29:33</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I Still use this spell (and its big brother "Holy Might") at level 34. Currently I'm in Dalnir and have had great success chain stunning the coerced spell casters. <BR>
<BR>
Right when you see the little blue message "insert mob name here begins to cast a spell", throw out your stun. By the time it wears off and the caster tries again, you will be able to throw out Holy Might. In effect, I am able to continually stun a caster until the meat shields kill it. The beauty is that it costs very little mana to cast either of these and my tanks very rarely, if ever, get hit by any offensive spells. It is also particularly useful against those darn Coerced Dwarves that like to heal their nasty little brethren<BR>
<BR>
Some of you may say that a cleric should only be medding and healing, and I would agree with you during fights with melee type mobs, but the low mana drain and very high success rate of disrupting the casters spells outweighs the gains in medding imho. Good hunting all<BR>
<BR>
Bikil Boneknitter<BR>
34 Cleric "Elder Blades"<BR>
Erollisi Marr<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
